vd clinics in the early 1960s when venereal diseases were 
virtually wiped out and to the lack of education about the 
diseases backward medical equipment and treatment and lax 
enforcement of the ban on prostitution 
it suggested that a national body with representatives from 
public security the judiciary civil affairs the womens 
federation the tourist industry and the public health sector be 
set up to prevent and treat venereal diseases 
laws and regulations should be tightened to ban prostitution 
and sufferers should be compelled to get medical treatment the 
